---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import AccordionItem from "../../components/ui/AccordionItem.astro";

import seoImg from "../../assets/pics/rewire.webp";

---

<MainLayout 
  title="Emergency Lighting Installation in Croydon – Certified Systems for Commercial & Residential Safety"
  description="Professional emergency lighting installation in Croydon. Commercial & residential safety systems, BS5266 compliant, certified installers. Free quotes & full compliance with UK fire safety regulations."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 mx-auto max-w-screen-xl lg:py-28 lg:px-6">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-medium mb-6 leading-tight">
          Emergency Lighting Installation in Croydon – Certified Systems for Commercial & Residential Safety
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg mb-8">
          We provide professional emergency lighting installation services in Croydon, ensuring businesses, landlords, and property managers—including commercial properties—meet legal safety requirements with fully certified systems. Whether you're upgrading existing lighting or installing a new system, we design and fit emergency lighting that protects occupants and ensures full compliance with UK fire safety laws and building regulations. All work is certified to meet industry and legal standards.
          <br/><br/>
          This is a dedicated secondary service under our main Electricians Croydon offering.
        </p>
        <a href="#contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-green text-white rounded-2xl font-medium text-lg hover:bg-dark hover:text-white transition-all">
          Get Free Quote — 020 3519 9989
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="[content-visibility:auto] [contain-intrinsic-size:400px] relative">
        <div class="bg-green rounded-[45px] p-1 md:p-2 relative z-10">
          <Image src={seoImg} alt="Emergency Lighting Installation in Croydon" class="w-full h-auto rounded-[35px]" />
        </div>
        <div class="absolute top-8 left-8 right-8 bottom-8 bg-dark rounded-[45px] -z-10"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- INTRODUCTION TO EMERGENCY LIGHTING SYSTEMS -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Introduction to Emergency Lighting Systems</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Emergency lighting systems are an essential part of any building's fire safety strategy, designed to provide reliable illumination when normal lighting fails due to a power failure or emergency situation. These lighting systems automatically activate during emergencies, ensuring that escape routes, stairwells, and exits remain visible and accessible.
      </p>
      <p>
        Emergency lighting installations are not just a best practice—they are a legal requirement in most commercial and residential buildings, helping to safeguard occupants and support safe evacuation procedures. By providing a dependable source of light during critical moments, emergency lighting systems play a vital role in preventing accidents and ensuring that everyone can exit the building safely, even in the most challenging circumstances.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COMPLETE EMERGENCY LIGHTING SERVICES -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Complete Emergency Lighting Services in Croydon</h2>
        <p class="mb-6">We install and maintain:</p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
                <use href="#icon-check"></use>
              </svg>
              <span>Emergency escape route lighting (a type of emergency escape lighting and escape lighting)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
                <use href="#icon-check"></use>
              </svg>
              <span>Open area (anti-panic) lighting</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
                <use href="#icon-check"></use>
              </svg>
              <span>High-risk task area lighting</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
                <use href="#icon-check"></use>
              </svg>
              <span>Maintained and non-maintained lighting systems</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
                <use href="#icon-check"></use>
              </svg>
              <span>Standalone and central battery systems</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
                <use href="#icon-check"></use>
              </svg>
              <span>LED emergency bulkheads, battens, and downlights</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
                <use href="#icon-check"></use>
              </svg>
              <span>Twin-spot floodlights for large spaces</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
                <use href="#icon-check"></use>
              </svg>
              <span>Recessed and surface-mounted emergency fittings</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-6">
          Each system is designed to comply with building layout, occupancy risk, and safety regulations. Communal areas such as lobbies and shared corridors are prioritized for emergency escape lighting to ensure safe evacuation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <Image src={seoImg} alt="Emergency Lighting Systems" class="rounded-[35px]" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHO NEEDS EMERGENCY LIGHTING -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Who Needs Emergency Lighting?</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">Our emergency lighting services are essential for:</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Commercial buildings with public access</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Offices and shared workspaces</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Shops, supermarkets, and retail units</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>HMOs and multi-let residential blocks</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Apartment buildings with shared stairwells or corridors</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Restaurants, pubs, hotels, and guesthouses</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Care homes, medical clinics, and schools</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Warehouses, workshops, and storage units</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-6 font-medium">Our service is trusted by both public and private sector clients for compliance and safety.</p>
      <p class="mt-4">
        If your property has escape routes or areas that become unsafe during a power cut, emergency lighting is not optional—it's mandatory.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- UK LEGAL REQUIREMENTS AND COMPLIANCE -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">UK Legal Requirements and Compliance</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">We design and install systems in line with:</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>BS 5266-1:2016 Emergency Lighting Code of Practice</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>BS EN 1838 for lighting performance and illumination levels</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>The Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Health and Safety at Work etc. Act 1974</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Local Authority Building Control (LABC) guidance</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Fire Risk Assessment requirements</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-6">
        Compliance with emergency lighting regulations and Building Regulations to ensure all installations meet current legal standards.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-8 mb-4">Our team issues:</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Commissioning certificates</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Emergency lighting logbooks</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Testing schedules and asset registers</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>EIC or MEIWC for associated electrical work</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-6 font-medium">All systems are designed and installed by qualified emergency lighting engineers to guarantee compliance and safety.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BENEFITS OF EMERGENCY LIGHTING INSTALLATIONS -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Benefits of Emergency Lighting Installations</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Investing in emergency lighting installations offers a wide range of benefits for building owners, managers, and occupants. First and foremost, emergency lighting enhances fire safety by providing a clear, illuminated path to safety during power outages, fires, or other emergency situations. This reduces the risk of trips, falls, and confusion, helping people to evacuate quickly and safely.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Emergency lighting is also a legal requirement under regulatory reform fire safety orders, ensuring that your building remains compliant with current legislation. In addition, well-designed emergency lighting installations help to minimize panic and anxiety during emergencies, offering reassurance and guidance when it's needed most.
      </p>
      <p>
        Finally, by maintaining visibility throughout the building, emergency lighting can help prevent damage to property and equipment during power failures, supporting overall safety and security.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- INSTALLATION PROCESS -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Installation Process – Step-by-Step</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">The emergency lighting installation process is a structured approach designed to ensure compliance with safety standards and minimize disruption to your business.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>Initial Consultation</strong> – We gather site details and use floor plans or perform a physical walk-through.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>Design Survey</strong> – Mapping escape routes, stairwells, exit signage, and risk areas.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>System Specification</strong> – Selection of fitting types, spacing, battery duration, and choosing a suitable system tailored to your building's specific needs.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>Quote Approval</strong> – Transparent costs including labour, equipment, and testing.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>Installation</strong> – Installing emergency lighting is scheduled with minimal disruption and carried out in accordance with safety standards; often completed in 1–2 days.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>Commissioning & Handover</strong> – System tested under mains failure; documentation supplied.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-6 font-medium">We work alongside your fire safety consultant or facilities manager where required.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TYPES OF EMERGENCY LIGHTING SYSTEMS -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Types of Emergency Lighting Systems</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>Maintained Emergency</strong> – These fittings operate continuously and stay lit during power loss (used in public buildings like cinemas, venues, or hospitals). Maintained emergency fittings provide reliable illumination both during normal operation and in the event of a power failure.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>Non Maintained Fittings</strong> – These fittings are usually off during normal operation and only activate when power fails (common in offices and stairwells). Their batteries are continuously charged to ensure they are ready to provide emergency lighting when needed.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>Sustained</strong> – Dual-lamp units that switch from mains to battery.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>Self-Contained (Single Point)</strong> – Each fitting has a built-in battery for ease of installation.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>Central Battery Systems</strong> – One location powers multiple lights; ideal for large buildings with maintenance access.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span><strong>Standby Lighting</strong> – Standby lighting is designed to allow normal activities to continue with minimal interruption during a power outage, unlike emergency escape lighting, which is specifically for safe evacuation and is a legal requirement.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-6">
        Most emergency lighting systems are designed to operate for a minimum of three hours during a power failure.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 font-medium">
        We recommend the right solution based on usage, building type, access, and ongoing maintenance capabilities.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FITTING TYPES AND PLACEMENT OPTIONS -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Fitting Types and Placement Options</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">We supply and install all emergency lights supplied in compliance with safety standards:</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Bulkhead emergency lights</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Twin spotlights for large open areas</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Emergency downlights for aesthetic ceiling finishes</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
